<title>GERMANY: German ZEW details 6-mth major nations forecasts.</title>
<headline>German ZEW details 6-mth major nations forecasts.</headline>
<dateline>MANNHEIM, Germany 1997-06-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following table lists the economic and market forecasts for the six months from June 25 issued by the ZEW Zentrum fuer Europaeische Wirtschaftsforschung GmbH research institute. The averages are compiled from a survey of 320 firms conducted from June 9-24.</p>
<p>					  Base    Forecast</p>
<p>INFLATION RATES (percent)</p>
<p>    Germany			    1.6     1.7</p>
<p>    U.S.				 2.2     2.4</p>
<p>    Japan				1.4     1.6</p>
<p>    Britain			    2.6     2.9</p>
<p>    France			     0.9     1.0</p>
<p>    Italy				1.6     1.7</p>
<p>SHORT-TERM RATES (Three-month interbank rates)</p>
<p>    Germany			    3.1     3.2</p>
<p>    U.S.				 4.9     5.3</p>
<p>    Japan				0.6     1.0</p>
<p>    Britain			    6.7     7.2</p>
<p>    France			     3.4     3.5</p>
<p>    Italy				6.8     6.8</p>
<p>LONG-TERM RATES</p>
<p>    Germany			    5.7     5.9</p>
<p>    U.S.				 6.4     6.8</p>
<p>    Japan				2.5     3.0</p>
<p>    Britain			    7.1     7.5</p>
<p>    France			     5.7     6.0</p>
<p>    Italy				7.1     7.3</p>
<p>BOURSE</p>
<p>    German DAX		     3,730   3,810</p>
<p>    U.S. Dow Jones		 7,670   7,720</p>
<p>    Japan Nikkei		  20,400  21,800</p>
<p>    Britain FT-SE 100	    4,660   4,690</p>
<p>    France CAC-40		  2,740   2,810</p>
<p>    Italy MIBtel		  12,700  13,300</p>
<p>EXCHANGE RATES VS MARK</p>
<p>    Swiss franc		     1.20    1.21</p>
<p>    U.S. dollar		     1.73    1.81</p>
<p>    Japanese yen		    1.52    1.55</p>
<p>    British pound		   2.83    2.85</p>
<p>    French franc		    2.96    2.96</p>
<p>    Italian lira		    1.02    1.02</p>
